colwidth="35.5">3</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="227.5">3 Mana</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="35.5">4</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="227.5">4 Mana</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="35.5">5</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="227.5">5 Mana</Cell></Table></tableblock> <h2>Challenges</h2> <p1>The Sunriders live a hard life revolving around their steeds, livestock, warfare, and hunting.  Obstacles revolve around these themes  Obstacles should keep these themes in mind.</p1> <challenge>Impress Ganghal, Hogel, and Ile at the Millet Plains</challenge> <p1>When the heroes initially visit the Sunriders, they are invited to visit the ranches and farms under Hogels stead in Millet Plains.  Arban is not there, but other important leaders are present, and grill the heroes over a feast of lamb.</p1> <challenge>Ganghal Challenges One of the Heroes to a Wrestling Match</challenge> <p1>Ganghal challenges the strongest and most powerful looking hero to a wrestling match, trying to prove his superiority in an important custom.  The match takes place at dusk.</p1> <challenge>Riding with Arban</challenge> <p1>When the heroes suitably impress the other Sunrider leaders, they are granted council with Arban, who invites them on a ride.  He is particularly interested in how they can handle riding the great distances over his steppes.</p1> <challenge>Fighting Off Drakes</challenge> <p1>During a ride or while out tending livestock, the group is set upon by fire drakes, large and fast carnivorous lizards which surround and attack.</p1> <challenge>Discussion of Tactics with Ganghal</challenge> <p1>Ganghal is interested in hearing the heroes approach to dealing with the Autarch, and if they consider her a legitimate threat or not.  He is looking particularly at their understanding of battle.</p1> <challenge>Helping with Hogel’s Herd</challenge> <p1>A large storm can be detected off in the distance, and the heroes must help Hogel secure the livestock.</p1> <h3>Other Challenges</h3> <ul><l1>Avoid Being Tricked By Hogel Into a Bad Deal</l1> <l1>Help Ile Harness Mana from Song Bluff</l1> <l1>Repel Moonrider Bandits</l1> <l1>Help Dashal Tend to a Sick Horse</l1></ul> <h1>Infiltration</h1> <h1>Skirmish</h1> <h1>Warfare</h1> <p1>Aside from a full strength Imperial force, the Sunriders possess the most dominant military in the land.  Their ability to maneuver about the battlefield on horseback while pelting the enemy with arrows is greatly feared.</p1>	 <h2>Units</h2> <p1>The Sunriders have access to a special unit type, from which their name derives.  These are highly trained cavalry capable of shooting accurately while moving about the battlefield, combining the best of both archers and cavalry.</p1> <statblock><Table xmlns:aid="http://ns.adobe.com/AdobeInDesign/4.0/" aid:table="table" aid:trows="12" aid:tcols="2"><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="2"><strong>Sunriders</strong> </Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="88.29999999999998"><b>Type</b></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="174.70000000000002">Unit</Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="88.29999999999998"><b>Morale</b></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="174.70000000000002"><fate>2</fate></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="88.29999999999998"><b>Mental</b></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="174.70000000000002"><fate>4</fate></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="88.29999999999998"><b>Consequences</b></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" aid:crows="1" aid:ccols="1" aid:ccolwidth="174.70000000000002">-2 <fate>1</fate> -2 <fate>1</fate></Cell><Cell aid:table="cell" ai